The following issues arise on this application:
i) Whether the Respondent has failed to fulfill its duty to decide the Applicant's application for permanent residence in a timely manner;
ii) Whether the Respondent should accept the Applicant's United States P.R. card as a valid identity or travel document for the purposes of paragraph 50(1)(c) of the
Immigration and Refugee Protection Regulations
, SOR/2002-227 (Regulations); and
iii) Whether an order in the nature of mandamus is an appropriate remedy in these circumstances;
iv) Whether this application is now moot because the Applicant has now been granted a permanent residence visa;
v) Whether the Applicant should be awarded costs.
STATUTORY PROVISIONS

